[1] Global - GPEI/WHO WPV1 (ES Pakistan) cVDPV1 (ES Madagascar), cVDPV2 (AFP Nigeria)
Date: Wed 18 Aug 2021
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative / WHO
https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliovirus Weekly Update as of 18 Aug 2021, World Health Organization

New wild poliovirus isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 0
Environment: 1
Others: 0

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 26
Environment: 1
Others: 9

Summary of new WPV and cVDPV this week (AFP cases and ES positives):
- Pakistan: 1 WPV1 positive environmental sample
- Madagascar: 1 cVDPV1 positive environmental sample
- Nigeria: 26 cVDPV2 cases

Afghanistan
- No wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) case was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in 2021 while the total number of 2020 cases remains at 56.
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2021 cases remains 43. There were 308 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.

Pakistan
- No wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) case was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in 2021. The total number of 2020 cases remains at 84.
- 1 WPV1 positive environmental sample was reported in KPTD.
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2021 cases remains at 8. There were 135 cases reported in 2020.

Angola
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 3 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.
Benin
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021 so far. There were 3 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020. These cases are all linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria.

Burkina Faso
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021 so far. The number of 2020 cases remains at 65. The country is affected by different outbreaks, 1 linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria and 1 to the Savanes outbreak in Togo.

Cameroon
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 7 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.

Central African Republic
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 4 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.

Chad
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 99 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020 from 3 different outbreaks.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across the Lake Chad subregion remains high.

Congo
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021. There were 2 cases reported in 2020.

Cote d'Ivoire
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2020 cases remains at 61.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DR Congo)
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 10 cases reported in 2021 so far. The total number of 2020 cases remains at 81.

Egypt
- No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 10 positive samples reported in 2021. There was 1 positive sample reported in 2020.

Ethiopia
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 7 cases reported in 2021 so far. The total number of 2020 cases remains at 36.

Gambia
- No cVDPV2 positive environmental samples was reported this week. 2 positive samples linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria are reported in 2021 so far.

Ghana
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 12 cases reported in 2020.

Guinea
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 6 cases in 2021 so far. The total number of 2020 cases remains at 44.

Kenya
- No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There was 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample reported in 2020 and 1 in 2021. The virus is linked to the Banadir outbreak in Somalia.

Liberia
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cVDPV2 cases in the country.

Madagascar
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) was reported this week. There are 6 cases in 2021 and 2 from 2020.
- 1 cVDPV1 positive environmental sample was reported in Boeni.

Malaysia
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) was reported this week. There was 1 case in 2020.

Mali
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2020 cases is now 50.

Niger
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2020 cases remains at 10.

Nigeria
- 26 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported: 1 each in Bauchi, Gombe, Kaduna, Sokoto and Zamfara, 2 in Kano, 3 each in Borno and Yobe, and 13 in Jigawa. There are 94 cases reported in 2021 so far. There were 8 cases reported in 2020.

Senegal
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2021 cases remains at 13.

Sierra Leone
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 4 cases in 2021 while the number of 2020 cases remains at 10.

Somalia
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 14 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.

South Sudan
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 59 cVDPV2 cases in the country; 9 in 2021 and 50 in 2020.

Sudan
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2020 cases remains at 58. The initial viruses were linked to the ongoing outbreak in Chad followed by local transmission.

Tajikistan
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2021 cases remains 23. There was 1 case reported in 2020.

Togo
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 9 cases reported in 2020.

Uganda
- No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. 2 positive samples linked to the N'Djamena outbreak in Chad are reported in 2021 so far.

Yemen
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) was reported this week. There are 3 cases reported in 2021 so far and a total of 35 altogether.

Officially reported WPV1 and cVDPV cases as of 17 Aug 2021
Wild poliovirus (WPV)
- Total global WPV1 cases in 2021: 2 (compared with 97 for the same period in 2020)
- Total global WPV1 cases in 2020: 140

Circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus (cVDPV) cases
- Total global cVDPV cases in 2021: 235 (compared with 278 for the same period in 2020)
- Total global cVDPV cases in 2020: 1105

