[Repeating my mod comment in Poliomyelitis update (19): global (cVDPV2) Gambia, Pakistan, RFI 20210813.8591368, "In the 30 Jul 2021 update from the Global Polio Eradication Initiative (GPEI), there were 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples reported in the Western Region. The isolates were identified as genetically linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria (see Poliomyelitis update (17): global (cVDPV1,cVDPV2 Uganda/Gambia) Pakistan, Nigeria 20210730.8557717)." Noteworthy is the mention that environmental sampling began in May 2021. No further positive ESs have been identified since the report on 30 Jul 2021. Hopefully the planned vaccination response to these findings will interrupt transmission and circulation of the cVDPV2.

Maps of Gambia showing regions can be found at: https://www.mapsland.com/maps/africa/gambia/large-detailed-political-and-administrative-map-of-gambia-with-roads-cities-and-airports.jpg and https://www.pinterest.com/pin/547680004656731040/. - Mod.MPP]

